nd strict no-partial-write output semantics; add parity harness `tests/test_tokenizer_bpe_token_pair_rank_lookup_checked.py` over hit/miss/boundary and randomized table-search vectors (WS6-02, WS6-05)\n554:- [ ] IQ-355 Implement HolyC helper `TokenizerBPEMergeApplyAtIndexChecked` in `src/tokenizer/bpe.HC` to merge one adjacent token-pair in-place within a token-ID span (left index + right index collapse with tail compaction), with checked span/index/capacity guards and strict no-partial-write semantics; add parity harness `tests/test_tokenizer_bpe_merge_apply_at_index_checked.py` against deterministic merge-state reference vectors (WS6-02, WS6-05)\n555:- [ ] IQ-356 Implement HolyC helper `FPQ16TopKPrefixMassQ16CheckedDefault` in `src/math/softmax.HC` as canonical default-capacity wrapper over `FPQ16TopKPrefixMassQ16Checked` deriving `out_mass_capacity=k` with exact success/error/no-partial-write parity, plus parity harness `tests/test_softmax_topk_prefix_mass_q16_checked_default.py` against explicit-capacity reference vectors and adversarial bounds (WS7-02, WS7-03, WS1-01)\n--- first unchecked WS items ---\n45:- [ ] WS0-01 Create project structure (src/, tests/, models/, docs/, automation/)\n46:- [ ] WS0-02 Document GGUF format spec (from llama.cpp/gguf-py reference)\n47:- [ ] WS0-03 Document Q4_0 and Q8_0 quantization math (integer-only formulas)\n48:- [ ] WS0-04 Document LLaMA architecture (layer structure, tensor names, dimensions)\n49:- [ ] WS0-05 Create reference output corpus (llama.cpp outputs for known prompts+seeds)\n52:- [ ] WS1-01 Implement fixed-point arithmetic helpers (mul, div, shift, round)\n53:- [ ] WS1-02 Implement integer exp/log/sqrt approximations\n54:- [ ] WS1-03 Implement integer softmax approximation\n55:- [ ] WS1-04 Implement RMSNorm (integer path)\n56:- [ ] WS1-05 Add test harness for math functions (compare against reference)\n59:- [ ] WS2-01 Implement GGUF header parser (magic, version, tensor count, metadata count)\n60:- [ ] WS2-02 Implement GGUF metadata reader (key-value pairs, string/int/float/array types)\n61:- [ ] WS2-03 Implement GGUF tensor info reader (name, dims, type, offset)\n62:- [ ] WS2-04 Implement tensor data loader (read quantized blocks from file into memory)\n63:- [ ] WS2-05 Add GGUF validation tool (print model info, tensor list, total size)\n66:- [ ] WS3-01 Implement Q4_0 block structure (32 values per block, 1 scale float16)\n67:- [ ] WS3-02 Implement Q4_0 dequantize (block -> integer array)\n68:- [ ] WS3-03 Implement Q4_0 dot product (quantized vec * quantized vec -> scalar)\n69:- [ ] WS3-04 Implement Q8_0 block structure and dequantize\n70:- [ ] WS3-05 Implement Q8_0 dot product\n71:- [ ] WS3-06 AVX2 optimized Q4_0 dot product (inline asm)\n72:- [ ] WS3-07 AVX2 optimized Q8_0 dot product (inline asm)\n73:- [ ] WS3-08 Benchmark: Q4_0 dot product ops/sec (naive vs AVX2)\n76:- [ ] WS4-01 Implement naive matmul (quantized input, integer accumulator)\n77:- [ ] WS4-02 Implement row-major / col-major layout handling\n78:- [ ] WS4-03 AVX2 tiled matmul (cache-friendly blocking)\n79:- [ ] WS4-04 Implement element-wise operations (add, mul, scale)\n80:- [ ] WS4-05 Benchmark: matmul GOPS for typical LLM dimensions (4096x4096)\n83:- [ ] WS5-01 Implement RoPE (Rotary Position Embedding) in integer math\n84:- [ ] WS5-02 Implement GQA (Grouped Query Attention) — Q/K/V projection, score, softmax, output\n85:- [ ] WS5-03 Implement SwiGLU FFN (gate * up projection, silu activation, down projection)\n86:- [ ] WS5-04 Implement transformer block (attention + FFN + residual + RMSNorm)\n87:- [ ] WS5-05 Implement full forward pass (embed -> N blocks -> final norm -> logits)\n88:- [ ] WS5-06 Implement KV cache for autoregressive generation\n89:- [ ] WS5-07 Validation: compare logits against llama.cpp for first token of known prompt\n92:- [ ] WS6-01 Implement BPE vocabulary loader from GGUF metadata\n93:- [ ] WS6-02 Implement BPE encode (text -> token IDs)\n94:- [ ] WS6-03 Implement BPE decode (token I